[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":2031},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F07\u002Fjavascript-global-vs-local-variables\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F07\u002Fjavascript-global-vs-local-variables\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F07\u002Fjavascript-global-vs-local-variables\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F07\u002Fjavascript-global-vs-local-variables\u002F":2007,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F07\u002Fjavascript-global-vs-local-variables\u002F":2016},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20190507\u002F3500556123\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1992,"date":1993,"description":1994,"extension":1995,"lang":1996,"meta":1997,"navigation":921,"path":1998,"readingMinutes":1999,"seo":2000,"standalone":2001,"stem":2002,"tags":2003,"tldr":2004,"updated":1993,"url":2005,"__hash__":2006},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fjavascript-global-vs-local-variables.md","Global vs Local Variables in JavaScript: The Trap That Catches Every Beginner","1001385828",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1979},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,63,70,79,127,134,140,149,152,203,206,262,268,281,335,344,348,364,418,429,433,439,494,497,549,562,565,632,645,649,652,657,664,667,800,804,807,810,1040,1043,1229,1232,1236,1239,1349,1352,1473,1492,1505,1514,1520,1589,1592,1765,1768,1952,1955,1961,1975],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"JavaScript has a lot of little traps that can knock a beginner flat — one careless step and you're standing on a landmine. So this post is all about the difference between global and local variables.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-difference-between-global-and-local-variables","The difference between global and local variables",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"Back in the day, whenever we created a variable we'd ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"var"," something.",[33,34,39],"pre",{"className":35,"code":36,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","var item = 'global mom';\n","js","",[28,40,41],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,43,46,49,53,56,60],"span",{"class":44,"line":45},"line",1,[42,47,30],{"class":48},"sWyjQ",[42,50,52],{"class":51},"sMAXC"," item ",[42,54,55],{"class":48},"=",[42,57,59],{"class":58},"sTRMh"," 'global mom'",[42,61,62],{"class":51},";\n",[17,64,65,66,69],{},"Log out ",[28,67,68],{},"item"," here and there's no problem at all — you get \"global mom\", no surprise.",[17,71,72,73,75,76,78],{},"Now what if we rewrite it like this? Create ",[28,74,68],{}," inside a function, then try to call ",[28,77,68],{}," from outside.",[33,80,82],{"className":35,"code":81,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"function testFu(){\n  var item = 'mom'\n};\nconsole.log(item);\n",[28,83,84,96,109,115],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,85,86,89,93],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,87,88],{"class":48},"function",[42,90,92],{"class":91},"sj_SG"," testFu",[42,94,95],{"class":51},"(){\n",[42,97,99,102,104,106],{"class":44,"line":98},2,[42,100,101],{"class":48},"  var",[42,103,52],{"class":51},[42,105,55],{"class":48},[42,107,108],{"class":58}," 'mom'\n",[42,110,112],{"class":44,"line":111},3,[42,113,114],{"class":51},"};\n",[42,116,118,121,124],{"class":44,"line":117},4,[42,119,120],{"class":51},"console.",[42,122,123],{"class":91},"log",[42,125,126],{"class":51},"(item);\n",[17,128,129,130,133],{},"You'll see it complain that ",[28,131,132],{},"item is not defined",".",[17,135,136],{},[137,138],"img",{"alt":132,"src":139},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FuivXzxo.png",[17,141,142,143,145,146,148],{},"These two tiny examples are pretty easy to read, and they show exactly where the problem is. This is global vs local variables at their most basic: a variable created inside a ",[28,144,88],{}," is what we call a \"local variable\", and anything outside the ",[28,147,88],{}," is a global variable.",[17,150,151],{},"Now that you've got the basics, try taking on the challenge below.",[33,153,155],{"className":35,"code":154,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var item = 'global mom';\nfunction name(){\n  item = 'local son';\n};\nconsole.log(item);\n",[28,156,157,169,178,190,194],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,158,159,161,163,165,167],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,160,30],{"class":48},[42,162,52],{"class":51},[42,164,55],{"class":48},[42,166,59],{"class":58},[42,168,62],{"class":51},[42,170,171,173,176],{"class":44,"line":98},[42,172,88],{"class":48},[42,174,175],{"class":91}," name",[42,177,95],{"class":51},[42,179,180,183,185,188],{"class":44,"line":111},[42,181,182],{"class":51},"  item ",[42,184,55],{"class":48},[42,186,187],{"class":58}," 'local son'",[42,189,62],{"class":51},[42,191,192],{"class":44,"line":117},[42,193,114],{"class":51},[42,195,197,199,201],{"class":44,"line":196},5,[42,198,120],{"class":51},[42,200,123],{"class":91},[42,202,126],{"class":51},[17,204,205],{},"I bet this one isn't hard — the answer is \"global mom\", because the function never actually got called. But what about this?",[33,207,209],{"className":35,"code":208,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var item = 'global mom';\nfunction name(){\n  item = 'local son';\n};\nname();\nconsole.log(item);\n",[28,210,211,223,231,241,245,253],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,212,213,215,217,219,221],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,214,30],{"class":48},[42,216,52],{"class":51},[42,218,55],{"class":48},[42,220,59],{"class":58},[42,222,62],{"class":51},[42,224,225,227,229],{"class":44,"line":98},[42,226,88],{"class":48},[42,228,175],{"class":91},[42,230,95],{"class":51},[42,232,233,235,237,239],{"class":44,"line":111},[42,234,182],{"class":51},[42,236,55],{"class":48},[42,238,187],{"class":58},[42,240,62],{"class":51},[42,242,243],{"class":44,"line":117},[42,244,114],{"class":51},[42,246,247,250],{"class":44,"line":196},[42,248,249],{"class":91},"name",[42,251,252],{"class":51},"();\n",[42,254,256,258,260],{"class":44,"line":255},6,[42,257,120],{"class":51},[42,259,123],{"class":91},[42,261,126],{"class":51},[17,263,264,265,267],{},"You'll notice ",[28,266,68],{}," becomes \"local son\". This situation is what we call variable pollution. (If \"local son\" was the result you expected all along, then fair enough — that's a different story.)",[17,269,270,271,274,275,277,278,280],{},"On top of that, if you try typing ",[28,272,273],{},"window"," you'll find a variable called ",[28,276,68],{}," sitting underneath it. Generally, when we write JavaScript we try as hard as we can not to pollute the global scope (window). Once you pile up too many global variables it hurts performance — every global variable needs memory to be stored — and it can even clash with other variables (name collisions). So a lot of the time we try to create variables inside a ",[28,279,88],{}," instead, like this:",[33,282,284],{"className":35,"code":283,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"function name(){\n  var item = 'local mom';\n  item = 'local son';\n};\nname();\nconsole.log(item);\n",[28,285,286,294,307,317,321,327],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,287,288,290,292],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,289,88],{"class":48},[42,291,175],{"class":91},[42,293,95],{"class":51},[42,295,296,298,300,302,305],{"class":44,"line":98},[42,297,101],{"class":48},[42,299,52],{"class":51},[42,301,55],{"class":48},[42,303,304],{"class":58}," 'local mom'",[42,306,62],{"class":51},[42,308,309,311,313,315],{"class":44,"line":111},[42,310,182],{"class":51},[42,312,55],{"class":48},[42,314,187],{"class":58},[42,316,62],{"class":51},[42,318,319],{"class":44,"line":117},[42,320,114],{"class":51},[42,322,323,325],{"class":44,"line":196},[42,324,249],{"class":91},[42,326,252],{"class":51},[42,328,329,331,333],{"class":44,"line":255},[42,330,120],{"class":51},[42,332,123],{"class":91},[42,334,126],{"class":51},[17,336,337,338,340,341,133],{},"Now you'll find ",[28,339,68],{}," is ",[28,342,343],{},"not defined",[17,345,346],{},[137,347],{"alt":132,"src":139},[17,349,350,351,353,354,356,357,360,361,363],{},"The reason is that the ",[28,352,68],{}," variable only lives inside the ",[28,355,88],{}," — the moment you leave the function, it gets released. So if you move the ",[28,358,359],{},"console.log"," inside the ",[28,362,88],{},", you'll see \"local son\" show up.",[33,365,367],{"className":35,"code":366,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"function name(){\n  var item = 'local mom';\n  item = 'local son';\n  console.log(item);\n};\nname();\n",[28,368,369,377,389,399,408,412],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,370,371,373,375],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,372,88],{"class":48},[42,374,175],{"class":91},[42,376,95],{"class":51},[42,378,379,381,383,385,387],{"class":44,"line":98},[42,380,101],{"class":48},[42,382,52],{"class":51},[42,384,55],{"class":48},[42,386,304],{"class":58},[42,388,62],{"class":51},[42,390,391,393,395,397],{"class":44,"line":111},[42,392,182],{"class":51},[42,394,55],{"class":48},[42,396,187],{"class":58},[42,398,62],{"class":51},[42,400,401,404,406],{"class":44,"line":117},[42,402,403],{"class":51},"  console.",[42,405,123],{"class":91},[42,407,126],{"class":51},[42,409,410],{"class":44,"line":196},[42,411,114],{"class":51},[42,413,414,416],{"class":44,"line":255},[42,415,249],{"class":91},[42,417,252],{"class":51},[17,419,420,421,423,424,426,427,133],{},"If you type ",[28,422,273],{}," now, you won't be able to find a variable called ",[28,425,68],{},". That's the whole idea of a local variable: it only gets stored within a specific environment, and the moment you go out to the global scope (window) or into another function, you'll get ",[28,428,343],{},[12,430,432],{"id":431},"another-global-vs-local-situation","Another global vs local situation",[17,434,435,436,438],{},"Now try this one. This time, what will the logged ",[28,437,68],{}," be?",[33,440,442],{"className":35,"code":441,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var item = 'global mom';\nfunction name(){\n  var item = 'local son';\n};\nname();\nconsole.log(item);\n",[28,443,444,456,464,476,480,486],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,445,446,448,450,452,454],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,447,30],{"class":48},[42,449,52],{"class":51},[42,451,55],{"class":48},[42,453,59],{"class":58},[42,455,62],{"class":51},[42,457,458,460,462],{"class":44,"line":98},[42,459,88],{"class":48},[42,461,175],{"class":91},[42,463,95],{"class":51},[42,465,466,468,470,472,474],{"class":44,"line":111},[42,467,101],{"class":48},[42,469,52],{"class":51},[42,471,55],{"class":48},[42,473,187],{"class":58},[42,475,62],{"class":51},[42,477,478],{"class":44,"line":117},[42,479,114],{"class":51},[42,481,482,484],{"class":44,"line":196},[42,483,249],{"class":91},[42,485,252],{"class":51},[42,487,488,490,492],{"class":44,"line":255},[42,489,120],{"class":51},[42,491,123],{"class":91},[42,493,126],{"class":51},[17,495,496],{},"The answer is \"global mom\". Some people start to get confused here — why isn't it \"local son\"? Isn't this the same as the earlier question?",[33,498,499],{"className":35,"code":208,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},[28,500,501,513,521,531,535,541],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,502,503,505,507,509,511],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,504,30],{"class":48},[42,506,52],{"class":51},[42,508,55],{"class":48},[42,510,59],{"class":58},[42,512,62],{"class":51},[42,514,515,517,519],{"class":44,"line":98},[42,516,88],{"class":48},[42,518,175],{"class":91},[42,520,95],{"class":51},[42,522,523,525,527,529],{"class":44,"line":111},[42,524,182],{"class":51},[42,526,55],{"class":48},[42,528,187],{"class":58},[42,530,62],{"class":51},[42,532,533],{"class":44,"line":117},[42,534,114],{"class":51},[42,536,537,539],{"class":44,"line":196},[42,538,249],{"class":91},[42,540,252],{"class":51},[42,542,543,545,547],{"class":44,"line":255},[42,544,120],{"class":51},[42,546,123],{"class":91},[42,548,126],{"class":51},[17,550,551,552,555,556,558,559,561],{},"The reason is that when ",[28,553,554],{},"name()"," runs, the ",[28,557,68],{}," inside it is creating a brand-new ",[28,560,68],{}," rather than directly using \"global mom\".",[17,563,564],{},"Next, what if we pass a value into the function instead? What's the answer this time?",[33,566,568],{"className":35,"code":567,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"var item = 'global mom';\nfunction name(item){\n  item = 'local dad';\n};\nname('local son');\nconsole.log(item);\n",[28,569,570,582,597,608,612,624],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,571,572,574,576,578,580],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,573,30],{"class":48},[42,575,52],{"class":51},[42,577,55],{"class":48},[42,579,59],{"class":58},[42,581,62],{"class":51},[42,583,584,586,588,591,594],{"class":44,"line":98},[42,585,88],{"class":48},[42,587,175],{"class":91},[42,589,590],{"class":51},"(",[42,592,68],{"class":593},"s_sBn",[42,595,596],{"class":51},"){\n",[42,598,599,601,603,606],{"class":44,"line":111},[42,600,182],{"class":51},[42,602,55],{"class":48},[42,604,605],{"class":58}," 'local dad'",[42,607,62],{"class":51},[42,609,610],{"class":44,"line":117},[42,611,114],{"class":51},[42,613,614,616,618,621],{"class":44,"line":196},[42,615,249],{"class":91},[42,617,590],{"class":51},[42,619,620],{"class":58},"'local son'",[42,622,623],{"class":51},");\n",[42,625,626,628,630],{"class":44,"line":255},[42,627,120],{"class":51},[42,629,123],{"class":91},[42,631,126],{"class":51},[17,633,634,635,360,637,639,640,360,642,644],{},"The answer is still \"global mom\". The main reason is that the ",[28,636,68],{},[28,638,88],{}," gets treated as the value passed in, so the ",[28,641,68],{},[28,643,88],{}," doesn't affect the global one. I know this part is a bit of a tongue-twister, but write it out a few more times and the logic gets clearer.",[12,646,648],{"id":647},"on-to-some-harder-challenge-questions","On to some harder challenge questions",[17,650,651],{},"These questions come from a fellow student in the Hexschool community.",[653,654,656],"h3",{"id":655},"question-1","Question 1",[17,658,659,660,663],{},"Try to read the code and call out what each ",[28,661,662],{},"console"," logs.",[17,665